    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Process receipts with Google Drive and MySQL in real time\n\n**Pattern:** File Processing · **Level:** Production · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nProcess receipts with Google Drive and MySQL in real time. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual summarization is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nDaily Schedule → Download from Google Drive → Parse CSV Contents → Clean & Reshape Rows → Rows Pass Validation? → Load Rows into Google Sheets → Repack as XLSX → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to file processing without manual effort\n- Anyone automating summarization in legal\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Scales without extra headcount\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2; Google OAuth2 / service account; MySQL connection; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "17e19c14-22c0-5436-0e51-8e0c32426fb3",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "b1b1aacb-81ec-650b-7ca3-e9fe0742f54d",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "81bb7c6d-2b92-b6f1-3ced-9861f9e1c4c5",
      "name": "🧹 Data quality"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your summarization process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 4
      },
